The Herald Senior Court Reporter A CABS employee stationed at the bank’s headquarters in Harare appeared in court on allegations of making false reports to the police that law enforcement agents had  extorted from him money he had been send with to purchase gold by a Harare businessman trading in the precious metal. Tanaka George Karonga (27) appeared at Bindura Magistrates Court charged with defeating or obstructing the court of justice. He was not asked to plead when he appeared before magistrate Ms Ethel Chichera who remanded him to June 8 for routine remand. Karonga allegedly lied that police at Bindura Police Station extorted him 179 grams of gold and US$350 on March 21. Ms Sheilla Maribha appeared for the State.